docs.lead_paragraph: THEY take off at 9:30 a.m., a squadron of 10 women power-walking briskly through the Garden State Plaza mall in their stretchy yoga pants and aerodynamic shoes, pushing Humvee-sized strollers. Past Nordstrom. Past the Godiva Chocolatier -- closed, thank heaven. Down to Lord & Taylor, where leader Christina Brigliadoro launches the morning's first cardiovascular routine. ''Two steps right, two steps left,'' she calls. ''Now, knee pulls. Four more, girls!''

headline.main: First Mall Rats, Now Stroller Brigades
